    Zero or more SourceEndExportFinalNodeEventListeners Injected. SourceEndExportFinalNodeEventListeners are used in situations when a node needs additional processing, even if an error was thrown during export.

    • exportNode

      public MigrationNode exportNode(QueueItem queueItem)
      Export the node into the source repository. The 'exportNode' method will be called unless #fireExportBeginNodeEvent(MigrationNode) returns true. If a listener does return true, we assume the listener has taken care of the export. Additional timers have been added for the totalThread, execTime
      Specified by:
      exportNode in interface MigrationSource
      See Also:
      MigrationSource.exportNode(com.tsgrp.migration.queue.QueueItem)

    • doExportNode

      protected abstract MigrationNode doExportNode(QueueItem queueItem)
      Create and populate the node defined by the given queueItem from the source repository. The exportNode(QueueItem) method takes care of firing events, etc.; implementing classes "just" need to implement the actual export/load logic.
      See Also:
      com.tsgrp.migration.source.MigrationSource#doExportNode
